29/09/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Spanish Foreign Ministry State Secretary Ramon de Miguel Egea visited Bucharest Friday (26 September) and reiterated his country's support for Romania's bid to join the EU in 2007. Egea, who met with President Ion Iliescu, Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana and other senior officials, said he saw no obstacle to Romania being recognised as a functioning market economy this year. (ACT Media - 29/09/03; Rompres - 27/09/03)
